(241, 1, '2014-03-18 08:55:02', '2014-03-18 02:25:02', 'Date: 8 July to 13 July 2013\r\n\r\nThere were 4 couples (Austrialian/spanish/chez/Franch ) stuck in Moreh for some days and they were brought to Thailand through Myanmar by us. Spent 6 days 5nights joyously in kalay/monywa/bagan/ yangon &amp; mawlamyaing cities and they amazingly feasted the nature and beauty of Myanmar. Among them S----- couple sent complements to their friends and praise our service rendered to the group. Reputation of us becomes higher and better due to the mouth- to - mouth complements of the customers.', 'Overland driving from India to Thailand through Myanmar', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '186-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-03-18 08:55:02', '2014-03-18 02:25:02', '', 186, 'http://192.168.0.123/brightviewtravel/186-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(253, 2, '2014-03-18 13:51:59', '2014-03-18 07:21:59', '<h1 style="text-align: left;"><strong>About Us</strong></h1>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">Established in 2008,owned and managed by an experienced tour operator,TIN MAUNG SHWE (photo attached). Worked in the Ministry of Hotels &amp; Tourism 14 years in various department;administration,finance and tour operation as a general manager,later handled the directive regulations as a Deputy Director General. Situated at no.20 A Aung San Stadium ( east wing ) upper pan so dan street,Mingalar Taung Nyunt township.,yangon , Myanmar.</p>\r\n\r\n<h1 style="text-align: left;"><span style="color: #000000;"><strong>OFFICE Address</strong></span></h1>\r\n<span style="color: #000000;">20A Aung San Stadium (East Wing)</span>\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"> Mingalar Taung Nyunt Township</span>\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"> Yangon Myanmar</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;">Tel : +95-1-394375, 394376</span>\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"> Fax : +95-1-394377</span>\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"> Email : tin.apex@gmail.com</span>', 'Contact Us', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '39-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-03-18 13:51:59', '2014-03-18 07:21:59', '', 39, 'http://192.168.0.123/brightviewtravel/39-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(245, 1, '2014-03-18 10:02:26', '2014-03-18 03:32:26', '<strong><a title="INDO-MYANMAR FRIENDSHIP CAR RALLY 2012" href="http://192.168.0.123/brightviewtravel/galleries/242/" target="_blank"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-197" alt="" src="http://192.168.0.123/brightviewtravel/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/IMG_0698.jpg" width="1936" height="1288" /></a>Date: (13 march to 21 march 2012 )</strong>\r\n\r\nJointly implemented by NorthEast Fedration on International Trade (NEFIT ) based in Guwahati,northeast India and Bright View T&amp; T from Myanmar side. 17 vehicles and 57 India plus 4 Myanmar participants were in this rally. The objectives were to promote friendship and trading among northeast India and Myanmar,especially for Mandalay and Sagaing region. During the trip officials and participants were made courtesy calls with chief ministers of Yangon/Mandalay/Sagaing regions. Also met with higher ranking officials from the ministry of commerce in Nay Pyi Taw and gala dinners were held respectively in Nay Pyi Taw, Yangon,Mandalay and Monywa attended by CMs and their cabinet members. The Embassy of India had also rendered a strong supports to this friendship event. We would say a do worthy and successful trip.\r\n\r\nAs an extended efforts so as to promote friendship &amp; trade among India, Myanmar and Thailand, NEFIT is trying to commence India-Myanmar - Thailand car rally in 2014', 'Indo-Myanmar Friendship Car Rally 2012', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '173-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-03-18 10:02:26', '2014-03-18 03:32:26', '', 173, 'http://192.168.0.123/brightviewtravel/173-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
