(411, 1, '2014-03-22 17:51:08', '2014-03-22 11:21:08', '<div style="width: 70%;">\r\n<h2>Myawaddy</h2>\r\nBorder entry point in Myanmar side adjacent to Maesot, Thailand. Border formalities to be done there within 45 minutes even for the 40/50 participants group, if your side prepared the needful documents in advance. For less than 15 pax group, it will take 15 minutes around.\r\n<h2>Hpa An</h2>\r\nCity of Kayin state where star-rated hotel rooms available, but not much sites to be seen. Used as night stop for exhausted travelers and who come late to Myawaddy.\r\n<h2>Golden Rock</h2>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><a href="http://locahost/brightviewtravel/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/MyanmarGoldenRock_03.jpg"><img class="alignright  wp-image-400" style="border: solid 7px #ddf;" alt="MyanmarGoldenRock_03" src="http://locahost/brightviewtravel/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/MyanmarGoldenRock_03-300x225.jpg" width="180" height="135" /></a>Really amazing scene, a big boulder perch atop of a brink and a small stupa on the boulder. All are gold glittered (that''s why we call it Golden Rock).No one can''t say the center of gravity of GR. You can see and feel a slight moving of big boulder. Another exciting thing is that you must leave cars and bikes at the base camp and take a local special truck to go up and down on the pretty steep motorway.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Sein le tin</h2>\r\nIt is a zoo garden resort (a mini zoo there) with adequate accommodation, located by the road side of highway. When the weather is clear, the Golden Rock pagoda can be seen from its tower.\r\n<h2>115-mile Travellers'' Inn</h2>\r\nLocated by the new express high way with caterings cum adequate accommodations. Many other restaurants around and a refueling station which provides quality service is near it.\r\n<h2>Nay Pyi Taw</h2>\r\nA new capital of Myanmar inaugurated in 2005 November, we would say administrative city. The president office and all ministries are situated there only. Nearly 60 hotels including 4 stars ratings. The attractions for the visitors are a big pagoda (which is almost similar to the world famous Shwedagon pagoda of Yangon) and Hlut Taw (Parliament) buildings.\r\n<h2>Taung gu</h2>\r\nAn old capital of second Myanmar empire, but very few ancient artifacts left. We would say a transit night stop. Good and normal accommodation facilities available.\r\n<h2>Meik hti lar</h2>\r\nA junction point situated on the old high way crossing Bagan to Inlay road and Yangon to Mandalay.\r\n<h2>Mandalay</h2>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><a href="http://locahost/brightviewtravel/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/upein.jpg"><img class=" wp-image-408 alignright" style="border:solid 7px #ddf;" alt="upein" src="http://locahost/brightviewtravel/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/upein-300x199.jpg" width="180" height="119" /></a>A last capital of Myanmar monarchs and cultural city. Can be seen lots of Myanmar artifacts, traditional and religious edifices both old and new. As the city is situated by the Ayarwaddy river, river going cruises and sunset &amp; evening meals on boat available. Also 4/5 stars rated hotels and other categories hotels abundant. The old golden palace, golden monastery and the world largest books are famous and sunrise / sunset scenes of U Bein bridge ( wooden bridge ) is a must for visitors.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Bagan</h2>\r\nAn ancient city of 11 AD situated by the Ayarwaddy river. Numerous artifacts of old pagodas to be seen at least 2 days for a rush traveler and at least 6 months for a researcher. Including 4/5 stars ratings and other classes accommodation facilities cum sorts of European /Chinese / Myanmar traditional foods available. Really a must for tourists.\r\n<h2>Inlay</h2>\r\nA big natural lake on Shan Plateau, 22km horizontal long and 10km vertical wide. A unique and traditional leg rowing of locals can be seen there only. Sufficient star rating hotels, traditional and all sorts of foods are available. Can visit and have a look round on the floating villages, hydroponics ,market places and a famous pagoda. Also silk weaving can be seen and get buy as souvenirs. Actually Inlay is a must for tourists.\r\n<h2>Mon ywa</h2>\r\nNot many places to visit except a Standing Buddha Statue which is supposed to be the tallest Buddha Statue in the world even though not recognized. It is said that structural design was made by a Myanmar citizen Chinese who works in NASA. Good accommodation available and we make night stops there due to distance &amp; traveling hours.\r\n<h2>Kalay</h2>\r\nJust a transit night stop because of its location. Accommodations are not good so far but best available n that area.\r\n<h2>Tamu</h2>\r\nA border check point small town in Myanmar side adjacent to Moreh. Just passing through for the formalities and not used to be night stop.\r\n<h2>Yangon</h2>\r\nOnce a capital of Myanmar till 2005 October, A second capital as of now with international airport and seaport. Until now it is a commercial city of Myanmar. Many interesting tourist sites with colonial buildings, market places, some other famous sites including The Great SHWE DA GON Pagoda which is to be enlisted in the World Wonders.\r\n\r\n</div>', 'Destinations in Brief', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '386-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-03-22 17:51:08', '2014-03-22 11:21:08', '', 386, 'http://locahost/brightviewtravel/386-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
