(504, 1, '2014-03-22 20:00:45', '2014-03-22 13:30:45', 'Date: 25 feburary to 5 march 2014\r\n\r\n3 couples ( Swiss / Spanish / Australian ) came in from Maesot on 3 motorbikes and one landrover and visited along mwd /golden rock /taung gu /mandalay / bagan /monywa / kalay /tamu route and proceeded to India. Among them petra &amp; Anders were quite satisfied with our service and they are going to write about us in their website "www.<a href="http://twobikersoneworld.com/" target="_blank">twobikersoneworld.com</a>"  very soon.\r\n\r\n<img class="ngg_displayed_gallery mceItem" alt="" src="http://192.168.0.123/brightviewtravel/nextgen-attach_to_post/preview/id--503" />', 'Overland driving Myanmar from Thailand to India', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '229-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-03-22 20:00:45', '2014-03-22 13:30:45', '', 229, 'http://192.168.0.123/brightviewtravel/229-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(505, 1, '2014-03-22 20:05:02', '2014-03-22 13:35:02', 'The followings are important facts to be reckoned with.\r\n<h2><strong>1. Up Climbing and Down Going Days</strong></h2>\r\nAs the road on Daw na range between Hpa an and Myawaddy is narrow, especiall cars cannot drive two and for everyday. So up and down days are alternative accordingly. Up climbing means from Hpa an to Myawaddy. Down going means from Myawaddy to Hpa an.\r\n\r\n<strong>April -</strong> odd days are up climbing &amp; even days down going.\r\n<strong>May -</strong> odd days up climbing.\r\n<strong>June -</strong> even days up climbing.\r\n<strong>July -</strong> even days up climbing.\r\n<strong>August -</strong> odd days up climbing.\r\n<strong>September - </strong>even days up climbing.\r\n<strong>October -</strong> even days up climbing.\r\n<strong>November -</strong> odd days up climbing.\r\n<strong>December -</strong> odd days up climbing.\r\n\r\nFor incoming from Maesot, travellers to be at Myawaddy accordance with down going days.And who wants to visit to Golden Rock, should come to Mwd check point no later than 07: 30 am mst because the last truck leaves at 18: 00 mst from the base camp. Normally driving hours take 7 hrs around from Mwh to Hpn,but if there is some blockade on the Daw na range it will take more. So just to be on the safe side, travellers should come to the entry point intime,the earlier the better.\r\n\r\nFor the entry from India side who wants to proceed to Thailand should also take account with up and down days for departure to Thai side.\r\n<h2><strong>2. Tour cost</strong></h2>\r\nSome travellers said visiting Myanmar is very costly. Of course some regulations are not waived, Eg. a leading escort car is a must for a trip. Even one vehicle is needed an escorted leading car. During The Great Indian World Trip, participants are only 3 people on 1 SUV, anyway we had escorted them in a leading car with 4 people (1 from the handled tour agent, 1 from Ministry of Hotels &amp; Tourism, 1 driver and 1 guide) you may think of it as a ridiculous matter since 3 visitors were escorted with 4 people, but this is the regulation and no other choice except abide by the regulations.\r\nSo, costs of escorts and vehicle are like burden for the clients. If you come 1 or 2 participants, the cost may too high. So please try to organize at least 6/7 participants, at that you can enjoy a reasonable tour cost. The bigger numbers of participants come, the lower cost you enjoy because total incurred costs were divided by numbers of participants so as to get per pax cost.\r\n<h2><strong> 3. Conditions of the roads</strong></h2>\r\nWe would say most of the roads mentioned in itineraries are in good condition. But the following segments are not good, somewhere bad-\r\nA. Between Myawaddy and Hpa an, segment on Daw na range about 40 kms are not good, among them about 10 kms is bad. The rest all asphalt road.\r\nB. From Hpa an onward up to the junction point of old highway, all asphalt but narrow and serpentine in some parts. From there to Mandalay is a good road but should take care of local motorbikes, jay walkers, long vehicles and overtaking vehicles from opposite side because there is no divider n the middle of road.\r\nC. As for the new highway from Ygn, NPT to Mdy is made of cement concrete,6 lane divided in the middle, but speed limit is 100 kmh. Really dangerous especially in rainy season if drive more than 100 kmh.\r\nD. Nothing to be said about other segments, but have to mention regarding road condition between Kalay and Monywa. Out of 220 kms, about 120 km is asphalt, the remaining 50 km is not good,50 km is we would say bad especially in rainy season.\r\nBut this route is underway repairing, up grading and envisage all weather road standard in near future.\r\n<h2><strong>4. Procedure For Incoming to Myanmar By Overland Route</strong></h2>\r\nTravellers who wanted to come in to Myanmar by overland routes on their own motorbikes or cars ( suvs,camper vans &amp; so on ) should talk with Tin by mail for the itinerary. As itinerary has confirmed and travelers agreed for the tour package costings they must send the following documents in excel sheets -\r\n* particulars of the participants ... passport details including first page copy , visa page copy ( after receiving visa ) address and occupation.\r\n* particulars of the vehicles ...reg.no.,model / made / brand , engine no. , chasis no. , colour and 2 photos ( 1 front , 1 side )\r\nAfter receiving these particulars, Tin ''s office starts paperwork for special overland permission. Put up the letter to the Ministry of Hotels &amp; Tourism and MoHT proceeds to thd Government Office for approval. This procedure takes normally (at least ) 10 to 14 working days, but starting the paper works 3 weeks earlier than arrival is on the safe side.\r\n<h2><strong>5. Getting Overland Visa</strong></h2>\r\nAs and when the permission comes down from Authorities ,Tin''s office send to the participants ,also to respective Myanmar Embassies at the same time if it is necessary.\r\nAt that time , participants can apply visa at MEs.\r\nCommonly, most of the travelers used to apply overland visa at ME ( New Delhi ),some people apply at ME ( Khatmandu ). I would say ME ( K ) is easier than ND because respective MEs have their own practices. But not that difficult the visa these dsys if documents are completed.', 'Important Facts', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'important-facts', '', '', '2015-02-23 15:13:40', '2015-02-23 07:13:40', '', 0, 'http://locahost/brightviewtravel/?page_id=505', 0, 'page', '', 0),
